Body: Description: We have a report that is supposed to send daily activity for a folder, but it is sending a report with activity from over a week ago.  The analysis 'preview' shows blank data, but the results table and report have the stale data in it.
Steps to Reproduce Updated: Run the daily activity report
Next Steps Updated: zoom meeting to review NAM configuration

What We've Learned Updated: I reviewed the logs provided and dont' see any obvious signs of issues with the NEA job
The problem is liking with the collection of the activity data by NAM
I need to look at NAMs configuration to make sure it's successfully collecting the desired data daily.

• What is the impact of the issue on your business?
    • Bad Reporting
  • Who is affected by this issue?
    • The person receiving the report.
  • What steps to troubleshoot the issue have already been taken? 
    • Included in the original ticket description - so basically none so far
  • Is the sale data the same old data every day?
    • No, in fact today the results table is blank.
  • Has anything changed in your environment since the last time it worked?
    • I worked with your support team to update the license in Activity Monitor
  • When did this issue start? 
    • Last week.

The job that the client provided logs for is just a simple job that builds a custom table based on a filter applied to the SA_FSAC_DailyActivityView table

It then creates a report that is just that same table

It has another analysis task that does build a custom table with a different filter applied to the same SA_FSAC_DailyActivityView table, but it was disabled

 

Need to look at the FSAC job to make sure it's getting good data

Next Steps Updated: zoom meeting to review NAM configuration
Also need to confirm FSAC job is running without issue

What We've Learned Updated: I reviewed the logs provided and dont' see any obvious signs of issues with the NEA job

I reviewed NAM's configuration and it is configured to collected the desired data. I couldn't get NAM search to return data from the share, but I did find it in NAM's raw agent logs

I also founf the data in NEA's SQL database
-SA_FSAC_DailyActivityView

their analysis task filters that table to create a new table that is used to generate the report
--filters for isoutlookinterval|Yesterday|
--and not a particular user

originally configured by PS

everything looks good
make a test change and will wait until tomorrow to see if it's reported
